<DOC><DOCNO> AP880901-0211 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-01-88 2109EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Greece-Blackout 1stLd-Writethru a0697 09-01 0300</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Greece-Blackout, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0697,0310</SECOND><HEAD>Power Failure Blacks Out Half of Greece</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: UPDATES with power partially restored and explosion causingblackout, CORRECTS with no problems in subway, details. No pickup.^By KERIN HOPE</NOTE><BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE><DATELINE>ATHENS (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A power failure blacked out Athens and most ofsouthern Greece on Thursday night, snarling traffic in the capitaland knocking out radio and television.   However, power was restored to parts of Athens later in theevening.   Industry Ministry officials said the failure was caused by anexplosion in a switch at an electricity substation near thenorthern town of Larissa. The cause was not immediately known.   The damaged switch knocked out power to three of the four cablesserving the area south of Larissa.   The power was restored by later in the evening to outlyingdistricts of Athens and some areas of the city center.   Police said there were no immediate reports of looting.   Public Power Co. officials said it would be hours before thepower was completely restored.   State-run radio and television went off the air at first.However, the radio returned to the air 40 minutes later and urgedAthenians to remain calm.   Police earlier said an undetermined number of people werestranded on the city's subway line. However, a spokesman for thesystem said later that it operates on a different power grid andwas not affected by the blackout.   There was no immediate word on how many people might have beentrapped in elevators by the blackout, which occurred as manyAthenians were going home for dinner.   Traffic lights in Athens were knocked out, causing huge trafficjams in the city of 3.5 million people.   The Athens airport operated normally throughout the blackout.   A doctor said the city's hospitals were operating on backupgenerators.</TEXT></DOC>